As I lie here on this damn hospital bed on my back trying to figure out this damn laptop, thinking to myself, why can't I have my macho, man size computer where this demerol haze would make no difference as my stumpy calloused fingers would find the right keys on my own keyboard. The nurses got so exasperated chasing me all over the hospital as I sought out sunlight, coffee and cigarettes, that they loaned me this toy they call a computer on the promise that I behave myself. And all this, plus long distance toll charges so that I can keep an eye on the antics of one Doc Spatz.<br><br>
Doc, strange as it sounds, I haven't found a thing of which you wrote which offended or disrespected me in the least on this thread. Just gave us the opportunity to ponder 'n reflect. And I am sad to report that this is a big disappointment! After all I went through to check up on ya! Damn!<br><br>
Oh ya, I haven't figure how to access my e-mail from here. Double Damn!<br><br>
Hey Teach, what you wrote was really profound, but I'm gonna have to wait for no more buzz to figger out what it all means. Until then,.............................
